                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94111/98: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName type="venue">U. S. S. “<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Potomac</hi>,”</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-02T00:00:00">December 2 [<hi
                                rend="italic">1?</hi>], 1937—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received December
                        2—1:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Entirely approve your recommendations about possible declaration. Please see
                    Secretary of Treasury at once about his telegram to me about silver and
                    exchange. I am inclined to go along with his suggestions.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
